WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:19.484 align:middle line:10%
[BACKGROUND MUSIC]

00:00:19.484 --> 00:00:22.025 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA GARR: Hi, I'm Lisa Garr,
host of "Gaiam Inspirations,"

00:00:22.025 --> 00:00:25.275 align:middle line:10%
and welcome to our beautiful
Los Angeles studio.

00:00:25.275 --> 00:00:27.500 align:middle line:10%
There are a lot of weight
loss programs out there,

00:00:27.500 --> 00:00:30.270 align:middle line:10%
and many of them don't
work, quite frankly.

00:00:30.270 --> 00:00:32.580 align:middle line:10%
It's proven because
50% of people

00:00:32.580 --> 00:00:35.140 align:middle line:10%
gain their weight
back after most diets.

00:00:35.140 --> 00:00:36.990 align:middle line:90%
You know this if this is you.

00:00:36.990 --> 00:00:39.740 align:middle line:84%
And people actually lose
weight, and then they

00:00:39.740 --> 00:00:42.950 align:middle line:84%
put more on when they
go off of their diet.

00:00:42.950 --> 00:00:44.950 align:middle line:84%
So could you imagine
what your life would

00:00:44.950 --> 00:00:48.460 align:middle line:84%
look like if you actually
stopped spending so much time

00:00:48.460 --> 00:00:51.290 align:middle line:84%
and energy focusing
on your weight?

00:00:51.290 --> 00:00:52.915 align:middle line:10%
Well, joining me is
Colette Baron-Reid,

00:00:52.915 --> 00:00:55.690 align:middle line:10%
an internationally renowned
intuitive counselor

00:00:55.690 --> 00:00:57.610 align:middle line:10%
whose latest book
is called "Weight

00:00:57.610 --> 00:01:00.390 align:middle line:10%
Loss for People
Who Feel Too Much."

00:01:00.390 --> 00:01:02.790 align:middle line:10%
And there's a lot more than
weight loss in this book.

00:01:02.790 --> 00:01:06.030 align:middle line:10%
It's for anyone who feels
energy and basically takes

00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:07.460 align:middle line:10%
on the weight of the world.

00:01:07.460 --> 00:01:08.060 align:middle line:10%
Welcome.

00:01:08.060 --> 00:01:09.270 align:middle line:90%
Thank you for being here.

00:01:09.270 --> 00:01:10.686 align:middle line:84%
>>COLETTE BARON-REID:
Thanks Lisa.

00:01:10.686 --> 00:01:13.030 align:middle line:84%
It's so exciting to be here
this early in the morning.

00:01:13.030 --> 00:01:13.653 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:01:13.653 --> 00:01:14.236 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Great.

00:01:14.236 --> 00:01:15.040 align:middle line:90%
It's beautiful.

00:01:15.040 --> 00:01:18.334 align:middle line:84%
And it's so great to have
you in front of me in person.

00:01:18.334 --> 00:01:19.090 align:middle line:90%
It's fabulous.

00:01:19.090 --> 00:01:22.185 align:middle line:84%
So you have been an intuitive
your whole life, right?

00:01:22.185 --> 00:01:23.060 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: I have.

00:01:23.060 --> 00:01:24.670 align:middle line:10%
And actually,
that's what actually

00:01:24.670 --> 00:01:27.270 align:middle line:10%
segued into writing the book,
because of my experience.

00:01:27.270 --> 00:01:29.120 align:middle line:10%
And I'll talk about
that in a second.

00:01:29.120 --> 00:01:32.780 align:middle line:10%
But I've worked as an intuitive
counselor for 23 years.

00:01:32.780 --> 00:01:38.049 align:middle line:10%
And I found my ability when
I was a really small child.

00:01:38.049 --> 00:01:40.340 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to call it an
ability rather than a gift,

00:01:40.340 --> 00:01:42.190 align:middle line:84%
because it was
something that I just

00:01:42.190 --> 00:01:44.547 align:middle line:84%
think it's an aptitude
that some of us have.

00:01:44.547 --> 00:01:47.130 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I like that, because it
doesn't make it exclusive just

00:01:47.130 --> 00:01:47.760 align:middle line:90%
to you.

00:01:47.760 --> 00:01:50.424 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people have gifts,
but a lot more have abilities.

00:01:50.424 --> 00:01:51.340 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Exactly.

00:01:51.340 --> 00:01:55.210 align:middle line:84%
And it's also less precious,
if you will, right?

00:01:55.210 --> 00:01:56.450 align:middle line:90%
Or special.

00:01:56.450 --> 00:01:59.750 align:middle line:84%
So when I was a kid,
the first experience I

00:01:59.750 --> 00:02:02.870 align:middle line:84%
had with not knowing
where I ended

00:02:02.870 --> 00:02:05.970 align:middle line:84%
and others begin-- which is
what my book's about actually,

00:02:05.970 --> 00:02:06.470 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:02:06.470 --> 00:02:08.860 align:middle line:84%
Empathy overload-- was
when I was a small child.

00:02:08.860 --> 00:02:10.139 align:middle line:90%
And it came to me in dreams.

00:02:10.139 --> 00:02:13.400 align:middle line:84%
So my experience
of overconnecting

00:02:13.400 --> 00:02:15.785 align:middle line:84%
was shown to me in a
series of nightmares

00:02:15.785 --> 00:02:18.950 align:middle line:84%
that I used to have between
the ages of three and five

00:02:18.950 --> 00:02:21.825 align:middle line:84%
when I would dream about
the same scenario over

00:02:21.825 --> 00:02:22.450 align:middle line:90%
and over again.

00:02:22.450 --> 00:02:24.030 align:middle line:84%
I would see very
skeletal looking

00:02:24.030 --> 00:02:27.700 align:middle line:84%
man crying at a table with
a pile of teeth on one side

00:02:27.700 --> 00:02:30.047 align:middle line:84%
and a pile of metal on the
other, like gold or whatever.

00:02:30.047 --> 00:02:31.880 align:middle line:84%
I knew they were teeth
because I had started

00:02:31.880 --> 00:02:33.282 align:middle line:90%
losing my teeth at that point.

00:02:33.282 --> 00:02:33.566 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:02:33.566 --> 00:02:33.710 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:02:33.710 --> 00:02:34.810 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: Because
I mean, your three.

00:02:34.810 --> 00:02:35.700 align:middle line:90%
Like, what is that?

00:02:35.700 --> 00:02:36.200 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:02:36.200 --> 00:02:37.950 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: And then
the same man or men

00:02:37.950 --> 00:02:40.650 align:middle line:84%
like him being shoved into
a burning Easy Bake Oven.

00:02:40.650 --> 00:02:43.170 align:middle line:84%
OK, that's what I thought
it was because you translate

00:02:43.170 --> 00:02:47.647 align:middle line:84%
your experience, right, to
what you see in your home.

00:02:47.647 --> 00:02:49.230 align:middle line:84%
And I'd never seen
anything like this.

00:02:49.230 --> 00:02:52.390 align:middle line:84%
I saw body parts and
a very horrible smell.

00:02:52.390 --> 00:02:55.024 align:middle line:84%
Bottom line is, I had that
experience over two years.

00:02:55.024 --> 00:02:57.440 align:middle line:84%
My mother would not want to
pick me up when that happened.

00:02:57.440 --> 00:03:00.380 align:middle line:84%
It was the only dream when
I would tell her the dream,

00:03:00.380 --> 00:03:01.720 align:middle line:90%
she act-- tensed up.

00:03:01.720 --> 00:03:06.040 align:middle line:84%
And a little kid knows that
because we aren't separated.

00:03:06.040 --> 00:03:09.065 align:middle line:84%
Our sensitivity is very much
connected to our caregiver,

00:03:09.065 --> 00:03:09.930 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:03:09.930 --> 00:03:14.705 align:middle line:84%
So 20 years later, and my
mom had too much to drink,

00:03:14.705 --> 00:03:16.330 align:middle line:84%
I was wearing a cross
she had bought me

00:03:16.330 --> 00:03:19.650 align:middle line:90%
because I was raised Anglican.

00:03:19.650 --> 00:03:21.330 align:middle line:84%
Christian, we were
raised Christians.

00:03:21.330 --> 00:03:22.490 align:middle line:84%
And I was wearing
this beautiful cross

00:03:22.490 --> 00:03:23.735 align:middle line:90%
she had bought me in Berlin.

00:03:23.735 --> 00:03:25.100 align:middle line:90%
It was Russian, right?

00:03:25.100 --> 00:03:27.100 align:middle line:84%
And she just looked at
it and said, take it off.

00:03:27.100 --> 00:03:27.930 align:middle line:90%
And I went, why?

00:03:27.930 --> 00:03:29.594 align:middle line:84%
She goes, I want you
to take that off.

00:03:29.594 --> 00:03:30.260 align:middle line:90%
And I said, why?

00:03:30.260 --> 00:03:32.490 align:middle line:90%
Because, she said, you're a Jew.

00:03:32.490 --> 00:03:33.920 align:middle line:90%
And I went, what?

00:03:33.920 --> 00:03:37.320 align:middle line:84%
And she told me then, you
know that dream you had?

00:03:37.320 --> 00:03:40.000 align:middle line:84%
And she told me my grandfather
was killed in Dachau.

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:42.280 align:middle line:90%
He was a Parisian Jew.

00:03:42.280 --> 00:03:46.990 align:middle line:84%
And the dream I was having
was my mother's experience

00:03:46.990 --> 00:03:50.290 align:middle line:84%
in Berlin during the war where
she picked up body parts.

00:03:50.290 --> 00:03:52.390 align:middle line:84%
My grandfather was killed
in a concentration camp.

00:03:52.390 --> 00:03:54.500 align:middle line:90%
And we were actually Jews.

00:03:54.500 --> 00:03:55.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:03:55.040 --> 00:03:55.390 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Yeah.

00:03:55.390 --> 00:03:56.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's chilling.

00:03:56.390 --> 00:03:57.799 align:middle line:90%
That's chilling.

00:03:57.799 --> 00:03:58.590 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Wait.

00:03:58.590 --> 00:04:00.736 align:middle line:90%
But the best part was the teeth.

00:04:00.736 --> 00:04:01.324 align:middle line:90%
OK, wait.

00:04:01.324 --> 00:04:02.990 align:middle line:84%
Because the Easy Bake
Oven was of course

00:04:02.990 --> 00:04:06.620 align:middle line:84%
my way of translating the gas,
the ovens, burning, right?

00:04:06.620 --> 00:04:10.150 align:middle line:84%
And the teeth, well, it was
very common for SS officers

00:04:10.150 --> 00:04:12.660 align:middle line:84%
to pull the teeth of the
people they were going to gas.

00:04:12.660 --> 00:04:13.410 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: My God.

00:04:13.410 --> 00:04:16.630 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: And in order to
make trinkets for their wives

00:04:16.630 --> 00:04:19.320 align:middle line:84%
and girlfriends, they
turned it into jewelery.

00:04:19.320 --> 00:04:21.604 align:middle line:84%
So that was a very
specific indication that--

00:04:21.604 --> 00:04:22.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I did not know that.

00:04:22.770 --> 00:04:24.211 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people
did not know this.

00:04:24.211 --> 00:04:24.960 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Yes.

00:04:24.960 --> 00:04:25.510 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:04:25.510 --> 00:04:28.019 align:middle line:84%
So that was a very common--
so here's the bottom line.

00:04:28.019 --> 00:04:30.560 align:middle line:84%
We turned this into something
a little bit better as we went,

00:04:30.560 --> 00:04:31.493 align:middle line:90%
but not really.

00:04:31.493 --> 00:04:32.430 align:middle line:90%
It took a while.

00:04:32.430 --> 00:04:36.070 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I mean, so I'm
getting lost in this vision

00:04:36.070 --> 00:04:36.670 align:middle line:90%
that you had.

00:04:36.670 --> 00:04:38.170 align:middle line:84%
And that's a lot
to handle at three.

00:04:38.170 --> 00:04:38.450 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Yeah.

00:04:38.450 --> 00:04:39.520 align:middle line:90%
Well, three to five.

00:04:39.520 --> 00:04:40.030 align:middle line:90%
However--

00:04:40.030 --> 00:04:40.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Still.

00:04:40.230 --> 00:04:41.210 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: We
don't know what it is.

00:04:41.210 --> 00:04:42.090 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Still.

00:04:42.090 --> 00:04:45.184 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's
terrifying at that age.

00:04:45.184 --> 00:04:47.350 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: So I want to
thread this a little bit.

00:04:47.350 --> 00:04:48.485 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, it was terrifying.

00:04:48.485 --> 00:04:50.360 align:middle line:84%
Like all my other dreams
that were terrifying

00:04:50.360 --> 00:04:51.880 align:middle line:90%
were terrifying.

00:04:51.880 --> 00:04:55.140 align:middle line:84%
But I want to go into that
concept of empathy overload,

00:04:55.140 --> 00:04:57.560 align:middle line:84%
when you feel too much
of the environment.

00:04:57.560 --> 00:04:59.180 align:middle line:84%
Most intuitive
people-- and actually,

00:04:59.180 --> 00:05:01.800 align:middle line:84%
most of the population
right now are

00:05:01.800 --> 00:05:04.890 align:middle line:84%
being invited into
that hypervigilance

00:05:04.890 --> 00:05:08.390 align:middle line:84%
through things like social
media and the onslaught

00:05:08.390 --> 00:05:10.196 align:middle line:84%
of information in the
communication age.

00:05:10.196 --> 00:05:12.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It really does just
connect us through the wires.

00:05:12.570 --> 00:05:12.840 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:05:12.840 --> 00:05:14.720 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: It connects
and disconnects us

00:05:14.720 --> 00:05:15.840 align:middle line:90%
at the same time.

00:05:15.840 --> 00:05:18.720 align:middle line:84%
And that's something I'll
segue back into a little bit

00:05:18.720 --> 00:05:23.500 align:middle line:84%
later when I explain the book,
because from an early age, when

00:05:23.500 --> 00:05:26.719 align:middle line:84%
I did not want anybody to touch
me either was interesting,

00:05:26.719 --> 00:05:28.760 align:middle line:84%
because I would want to
put something in my mouth

00:05:28.760 --> 00:05:29.259 align:middle line:90%
right away.

00:05:29.259 --> 00:05:32.650 align:middle line:84%
I'd seriously, I'd would even
pick up my dog's dog biscuits

00:05:32.650 --> 00:05:35.310 align:middle line:84%
and stick it in my mouth if
somebody got too close to me.

00:05:35.310 --> 00:05:38.410 align:middle line:84%
So I used food to ground
myself from when I was a kid.

00:05:38.410 --> 00:05:40.639 align:middle line:84%
So I look back on that going,
oh, that's interesting.

00:05:40.639 --> 00:05:41.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Very interesting.

00:05:41.680 --> 00:05:43.680 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, because it
was dense and it--

00:05:43.680 --> 00:05:44.829 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: And physical.

00:05:44.829 --> 00:05:47.120 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you didn't know
that you were that impacted.

00:05:47.120 --> 00:05:48.286 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Oh my God, no.

00:05:48.286 --> 00:05:50.730 align:middle line:84%
I didn't even know what to
call that until recently.

00:05:50.730 --> 00:05:51.370 align:middle line:90%
No, no, no.

00:05:51.370 --> 00:05:52.745 align:middle line:84%
The experience is
the experience,

00:05:52.745 --> 00:05:55.080 align:middle line:84%
and you don't have anybody
telling you what it is.

00:05:55.080 --> 00:05:59.510 align:middle line:84%
So moving through life,
I had many experiences

00:05:59.510 --> 00:06:04.730 align:middle line:84%
like that where I would not know
where I ended and you began.

00:06:04.730 --> 00:06:07.480 align:middle line:84%
And the knowing that I
had about your information

00:06:07.480 --> 00:06:08.750 align:middle line:90%
was just available to me.

00:06:08.750 --> 00:06:11.540 align:middle line:84%
And I just thought, you've
just told me or I just knew it.

00:06:11.540 --> 00:06:15.070 align:middle line:84%
And it would be a constant
sense of, how did I know that?

00:06:15.070 --> 00:06:16.380 align:middle line:90%
Why do I know that?

00:06:16.380 --> 00:06:18.450 align:middle line:90%
What does that mean?

00:06:18.450 --> 00:06:20.890 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Too much information
at the same time, yes.

00:06:20.890 --> 00:06:22.440 align:middle line:90%
Because you get everything.

00:06:22.440 --> 00:06:24.542 align:middle line:84%
You get the dark, the
light, the past, the future.

00:06:24.542 --> 00:06:26.000 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: It's
just what it is.

00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:28.700 align:middle line:90%
And it's just available, right?

00:06:28.700 --> 00:06:30.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So let me just
talk to you about that.

00:06:30.900 --> 00:06:32.090 align:middle line:90%
So it's just available.

00:06:32.090 --> 00:06:34.600 align:middle line:84%
I have all of these
pictures floating around me

00:06:34.600 --> 00:06:35.470 align:middle line:90%
right now, right?

00:06:35.470 --> 00:06:35.800 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Right.

00:06:35.800 --> 00:06:38.110 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you can just
pick up and sense whatever

00:06:38.110 --> 00:06:41.260 align:middle line:84%
it is in my past, future,
problems, stories,

00:06:41.260 --> 00:06:42.090 align:middle line:90%
things like that?

00:06:42.090 --> 00:06:44.631 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: It's how I work
actually, interestingly enough.

00:06:44.631 --> 00:06:46.270 align:middle line:84%
I see pictures and
images and stories.

00:06:46.270 --> 00:06:50.720 align:middle line:84%
Now of course, I've turned this
into something professional

00:06:50.720 --> 00:06:52.020 align:middle line:90%
that can help other people.

00:06:52.020 --> 00:06:53.080 align:middle line:90%
I've honed it.

00:06:53.080 --> 00:06:54.080 align:middle line:90%
I've worked with it.

00:06:54.080 --> 00:06:55.010 align:middle line:90%
I know what it is now.

00:06:55.010 --> 00:06:55.950 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You've set
boundaries around it.

00:06:55.950 --> 00:06:58.040 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: And I've set very
strong boundaries around it.

00:06:58.040 --> 00:06:58.539 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:06:58.539 --> 00:07:01.260 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: But the feeling
piece is something else.

00:07:01.260 --> 00:07:03.300 align:middle line:84%
But the information
piece is how I've

00:07:03.300 --> 00:07:05.530 align:middle line:84%
made my living for
23 years, where

00:07:05.530 --> 00:07:11.740 align:middle line:84%
I will see the threads of
a tapestry of a person.

00:07:11.740 --> 00:07:13.360 align:middle line:90%
So what has affected you?

00:07:13.360 --> 00:07:15.180 align:middle line:90%
Where did that thread come from?

00:07:15.180 --> 00:07:18.100 align:middle line:84%
How are you making
that pattern today?

00:07:18.100 --> 00:07:19.960 align:middle line:84%
Have you changed
the pattern at all?

00:07:19.960 --> 00:07:20.820 align:middle line:90%
What did you do?

00:07:20.820 --> 00:07:23.010 align:middle line:84%
What came into your
life from others?

00:07:23.010 --> 00:07:24.700 align:middle line:84%
Because it's all
about synchronicities

00:07:24.700 --> 00:07:28.310 align:middle line:84%
and the web of potentiality,
where all of us

00:07:28.310 --> 00:07:32.680 align:middle line:84%
are somehow interconnected in
this extraordinary, vast sea

00:07:32.680 --> 00:07:33.410 align:middle line:90%
of possibilities.

00:07:33.410 --> 00:07:35.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's actually
beautiful the way you

00:07:35.030 --> 00:07:37.530 align:middle line:84%
that you put it, but I'm sure
it didn't read that way to you

00:07:37.530 --> 00:07:39.990 align:middle line:84%
when you were a
child and a teenager

00:07:39.990 --> 00:07:41.730 align:middle line:84%
where you didn't
understand what this was

00:07:41.730 --> 00:07:44.280 align:middle line:84%
and why all this information
was flooding into you.

00:07:44.280 --> 00:07:47.150 align:middle line:84%
So that, obviously,
made-- do you

00:07:47.150 --> 00:07:49.690 align:middle line:84%
think that that ability that
you had to sense and intuit

00:07:49.690 --> 00:07:54.300 align:middle line:84%
everything around you made
you feel that the smallest

00:07:54.300 --> 00:07:56.180 align:middle line:90%
things were amplified to you?

00:07:56.180 --> 00:07:57.550 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Totally.

00:07:57.550 --> 00:07:59.430 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:07:59.430 --> 00:08:02.160 align:middle line:84%
And amplified for
me emotionally.

00:08:02.160 --> 00:08:08.260 align:middle line:84%
