And you went to the
center after that.

00:16:29.280 --> 00:16:30.390 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: I
went to the center

00:16:30.390 --> 00:16:32.348 align:middle line:84%
and told them that I
needed to be deprogrammed,

00:16:32.348 --> 00:16:34.344 align:middle line:84%
that I had got an
evil spirit in me.

00:16:34.344 --> 00:16:34.844 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:16:34.844 --> 00:16:35.710 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, my goodness.

00:16:35.710 --> 00:16:37.300 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: And they
were like, mm hmm.

00:16:37.300 --> 00:16:38.425 align:middle line:84%
You're going to be
coming as an in-patient.

00:16:38.425 --> 00:16:39.320 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:16:39.320 --> 00:16:39.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:16:39.820 --> 00:16:42.028 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: And I just
needed to sleep for a month.

00:16:42.028 --> 00:16:42.920 align:middle line:90%
That's what I said.

00:16:42.920 --> 00:16:44.500 align:middle line:84%
I absolutely-- they
thought I was hilarious.

00:16:44.500 --> 00:16:45.620 align:middle line:84%
Actually, they
thought I was the one

00:16:45.620 --> 00:16:47.075 align:middle line:84%
person that was
going to make it.

00:16:47.075 --> 00:16:47.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:16:47.700 --> 00:16:48.491 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Yeah.

00:16:48.491 --> 00:16:50.260 align:middle line:84%
They all cried when
I got my 30 days.

00:16:50.260 --> 00:16:52.300 align:middle line:84%
And when I got my
one year medallion

00:16:52.300 --> 00:16:55.240 align:middle line:84%
and when I got my
one year recovery,

00:16:55.240 --> 00:16:56.800 align:middle line:90%
all my counselors were there.

00:16:56.800 --> 00:17:02.110 align:middle line:84%
And on the 20th anniversary
of my 20th year,

00:17:02.110 --> 00:17:03.560 align:middle line:84%
and the 20th year
that they were--

00:17:03.560 --> 00:17:04.970 align:middle line:90%
I was 20 years clean and sober.

00:17:04.970 --> 00:17:07.010 align:middle line:84%
And when the center
was 20 years old

00:17:07.010 --> 00:17:09.599 align:middle line:84%
with the Minister of
Health Canada came,

00:17:09.599 --> 00:17:12.690 align:middle line:84%
I spoke at their 20
year anniversary.

00:17:12.690 --> 00:17:14.670 align:middle line:84%
It was just the most
extraordinary thing.

00:17:14.670 --> 00:17:16.000 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Well, I can imagine.

00:17:16.000 --> 00:17:18.200 align:middle line:84%
Because I was going to
say, did you ever go back?

00:17:18.200 --> 00:17:20.199 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: Or it was
the 15 year anniversary.

00:17:20.199 --> 00:17:20.760 align:middle line:90%
Sorry.

00:17:20.760 --> 00:17:23.177 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But you went back and
you were of service to them.

00:17:23.177 --> 00:17:24.134 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Oh, yeah.

00:17:24.134 --> 00:17:25.780 align:middle line:84%
I went back and did
service every year.

00:17:25.780 --> 00:17:29.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But you spoke
as a successful author

00:17:29.510 --> 00:17:33.310 align:middle line:84%
with best selling books and
record deals and book deals

00:17:33.310 --> 00:17:35.956 align:middle line:84%
and clean and sober
the entire way.

00:17:35.956 --> 00:17:37.330 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID:
Well, at that point

00:17:37.330 --> 00:17:39.705 align:middle line:84%
I hadn't gotten the book deal,
but I had the record deal.

00:17:39.705 --> 00:17:45.442 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, so that was an interesting
thing because, you know,

00:17:45.442 --> 00:17:46.920 align:middle line:90%
I am not special.

00:17:46.920 --> 00:17:48.920 align:middle line:84%
You need to know that
I am not special.

00:17:48.920 --> 00:17:53.650 align:middle line:84%
I don't believe that a magic
fairy came and sprinkled dust

00:17:53.650 --> 00:17:56.710 align:middle line:84%
on me and said,
now you're special.

00:17:56.710 --> 00:18:00.640 align:middle line:84%
I struggled and I
continue to struggle.

00:18:00.640 --> 00:18:04.540 align:middle line:90%
But I made my talents.

00:18:04.540 --> 00:18:11.150 align:middle line:84%
I allowed the talents that
I was given to be used.

00:18:11.150 --> 00:18:13.630 align:middle line:84%
I didn't get my record deal
until I was 40 years old.

00:18:13.630 --> 00:18:16.227 align:middle line:84%
And all that time I
was doing readings,

00:18:16.227 --> 00:18:17.810 align:middle line:84%
telling people I
don't really do this.

00:18:17.810 --> 00:18:19.330 align:middle line:90%
I'm really a singer.

00:18:19.330 --> 00:18:22.986 align:middle line:84%
And I had clients all over
the world at that point.

00:18:22.986 --> 00:18:24.360 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Doing
readings, because--

00:18:24.360 --> 00:18:24.710 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Yeah.

00:18:24.710 --> 00:18:27.200 align:middle line:84%
29 countries and I'm telling
them I don't really do this.

00:18:27.200 --> 00:18:28.067 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:18:28.067 --> 00:18:28.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:18:28.650 --> 00:18:31.000 align:middle line:90%
Well, I love what you just said.

00:18:31.000 --> 00:18:34.030 align:middle line:84%
I love that you said
that you are not special.

00:18:34.030 --> 00:18:39.780 align:middle line:84%
Because we all have those same
exact challenges, struggles,

00:18:39.780 --> 00:18:41.900 align:middle line:84%
whatever it is that
we're going through.

00:18:41.900 --> 00:18:42.950 align:middle line:90%
You're human.

00:18:42.950 --> 00:18:44.450 align:middle line:90%
We're human.

00:18:44.450 --> 00:18:48.910 align:middle line:84%
I mean, if anybody was
to live on a pedestal

00:18:48.910 --> 00:18:51.440 align:middle line:84%
their entire lives, it
would be impossible.

00:18:51.440 --> 00:18:54.560 align:middle line:84%
We've seen so many falls from
grace because people don't

00:18:54.560 --> 00:18:58.090 align:middle line:84%
understand that it's how
you deal with the day to day

00:18:58.090 --> 00:19:02.980 align:middle line:84%
challenges and struggles of
life that make you who you are.

00:19:02.980 --> 00:19:04.895 align:middle line:84%
And you become a better
person through how

00:19:04.895 --> 00:19:06.770 align:middle line:84%
you deal with those
struggles and challenges,

00:19:06.770 --> 00:19:09.320 align:middle line:84%
how you perceive those
struggles and challenges.

00:19:09.320 --> 00:19:13.791 align:middle line:84%
So how did you-- now as
I say you're healing,

00:19:13.791 --> 00:19:15.540 align:middle line:84%
and now that you're
able to talk about all

00:19:15.540 --> 00:19:20.810 align:middle line:84%
of this with the beautiful
candidly open healed posture,

00:19:20.810 --> 00:19:23.670 align:middle line:84%
how do you now look back
on that and tell somebody

00:19:23.670 --> 00:19:27.620 align:middle line:84%
who's been through that
where to get started?

00:19:27.620 --> 00:19:29.330 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: Well,
radical forgiveness

00:19:29.330 --> 00:19:31.130 align:middle line:90%
comes after radical acceptance.

00:19:31.130 --> 00:19:33.220 align:middle line:84%
And these are these two
things that I talk about.

00:19:33.220 --> 00:19:37.920 align:middle line:84%
And because, until I could
accept and really accept

00:19:37.920 --> 00:19:40.460 align:middle line:84%
that I was an addict and
an alcoholic, really--

00:19:40.460 --> 00:19:42.454 align:middle line:84%
and at that point,
too, I was starting

00:19:42.454 --> 00:19:44.620 align:middle line:84%
the empathy and the eating
thing started to come up.

00:19:44.620 --> 00:19:47.970 align:middle line:84%
So I was only dealing with
one thing at a time, right?

00:19:47.970 --> 00:19:49.597 align:middle line:84%
And then my parents
died back to back.

00:19:49.597 --> 00:19:50.680 align:middle line:90%
They lost all their money.

00:19:50.680 --> 00:19:52.640 align:middle line:84%
So I had a lot of
things to experience.

00:19:52.640 --> 00:19:53.994 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't like life got good.

00:19:53.994 --> 00:19:55.410 align:middle line:84%
Actually, a lot
of horrible things

00:19:55.410 --> 00:19:56.970 align:middle line:84%
happened after I
got clean and sober.

00:19:56.970 --> 00:19:57.300 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:19:57.300 --> 00:19:59.380 align:middle line:84%
And you didn't go back to
the addiction after that?

00:19:59.380 --> 00:19:59.760 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: No.

00:19:59.760 --> 00:20:00.140 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:20:00.140 --> 00:20:00.450 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:20:00.450 --> 00:20:01.140 align:middle line:90%
A day at a time.

00:20:01.140 --> 00:20:01.930 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:20:01.930 --> 00:20:03.830 align:middle line:90%
But it wasn't easy.

00:20:03.830 --> 00:20:08.216 align:middle line:90%
And my parents died paupers.

00:20:08.216 --> 00:20:09.450 align:middle line:90%
My mom had a brain tumor.

00:20:09.450 --> 00:20:12.160 align:middle line:84%
My dad got Alzheimer's
when he lost everything

00:20:12.160 --> 00:20:13.210 align:middle line:90%
in real estate deal.

00:20:13.210 --> 00:20:14.200 align:middle line:90%
Millions of dollars.

00:20:14.200 --> 00:20:17.660 align:middle line:84%
And my parents became
completely impoverished.

00:20:17.660 --> 00:20:19.810 align:middle line:90%
So we had to deal with that.

00:20:19.810 --> 00:20:22.490 align:middle line:90%


00:20:22.490 --> 00:20:25.500 align:middle line:84%
So really the grace is
the unmerited gift, right?

00:20:25.500 --> 00:20:27.590 align:middle line:84%
So I really believe
that grace is something

00:20:27.590 --> 00:20:30.830 align:middle line:84%
that is not to be put
on pedestals with.

00:20:30.830 --> 00:20:34.800 align:middle line:84%
The fall from grace is really
with a fall from humility.

00:20:34.800 --> 00:20:40.220 align:middle line:84%
So for me, the reminder
of the humility

00:20:40.220 --> 00:20:44.210 align:middle line:84%
of life on life's terms, we can
create our own reality, yes.

00:20:44.210 --> 00:20:48.270 align:middle line:84%
But that reality is based on
how we respond, not the fact

00:20:48.270 --> 00:20:51.070 align:middle line:84%
that we can wiggle our
noses and get what we want.

00:20:51.070 --> 00:20:53.220 align:middle line:84%
It's how do we respond
to the challenges

00:20:53.220 --> 00:20:56.890 align:middle line:84%
as we are moving forward to
manifest the reality that we

00:20:56.890 --> 00:20:57.840 align:middle line:90%
desire, right?

00:20:57.840 --> 00:20:58.340 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:20:58.340 --> 00:21:00.814 align:middle line:84%
And that response happens when
you look at it differently.

00:21:00.814 --> 00:21:01.730 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Exactly.

00:21:01.730 --> 00:21:03.188 align:middle line:84%
You have to look
at it differently.

00:21:03.188 --> 00:21:05.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Your perception
of it has to be.

00:21:05.190 --> 00:21:07.790 align:middle line:84%
But when you are
empathizing and feeling

00:21:07.790 --> 00:21:10.050 align:middle line:84%
and the boundaries
are all blurred

00:21:10.050 --> 00:21:11.820 align:middle line:84%
and you're trying
to convince yourself

00:21:11.820 --> 00:21:15.090 align:middle line:84%
to look at it in a different
way, you feel crazy.

00:21:15.090 --> 00:21:18.010 align:middle line:90%
I mean, how do you do that?

00:21:18.010 --> 00:21:19.920 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: Well,
I don't know if you

00:21:19.920 --> 00:21:22.630 align:middle line:84%
feel crazy so much
as-- first of all.

00:21:22.630 --> 00:21:25.175 align:middle line:84%
OK, so we're talking about a
number of different threads,

00:21:25.175 --> 00:21:25.675 align:middle line:90%
if you will.

00:21:25.675 --> 00:21:27.830 align:middle line:84%
So it's getting a little
bit of a hairball right now.

00:21:27.830 --> 00:21:29.913 align:middle line:84%
We have to make sure we
don't make it all tied up,

00:21:29.913 --> 00:21:30.451 align:middle line:90%
but we can.

00:21:30.451 --> 00:21:30.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:21:30.950 --> 00:21:32.610 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: We can separate
them out a little bit

00:21:32.610 --> 00:21:33.330 align:middle line:90%
to understand it.

00:21:33.330 --> 00:21:34.340 align:middle line:90%
So, OK.

00:21:34.340 --> 00:21:36.300 align:middle line:84%
So the feeling too
much aspect which

00:21:36.300 --> 00:21:39.770 align:middle line:84%
of course led to this
latest book, for example,

00:21:39.770 --> 00:21:44.280 align:middle line:84%
was what I recognized
was an issue.

00:21:44.280 --> 00:21:46.972 align:middle line:84%
Because I started having
issues with my weight, OK?

00:21:46.972 --> 00:21:48.930 align:middle line:84%
So with all of this, when
I was doing readings,

00:21:48.930 --> 00:21:50.900 align:middle line:84%
I'd be going up and
down like an accordion

00:21:50.900 --> 00:21:53.000 align:middle line:84%
and feeling really
terrible about myself.

00:21:53.000 --> 00:21:56.360 align:middle line:84%
And then I gained 85
pounds when my mother died.

00:21:56.360 --> 00:21:57.320 align:middle line:90%
I want to go there.

00:21:57.320 --> 00:21:58.857 align:middle line:84%
Because I was doing
readings, trying

00:21:58.857 --> 00:22:00.690 align:middle line:84%
to become a singer--
which I had to give up,

00:22:00.690 --> 00:22:02.481 align:middle line:84%
by the way, because it
just wasn't working.

00:22:02.481 --> 00:22:03.214 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:22:03.214 --> 00:22:04.880 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: And
people were calling me

00:22:04.880 --> 00:22:05.960 align:middle line:84%
for readings from
all over the world,

00:22:05.960 --> 00:22:07.820 align:middle line:84%
and I never gave
out a business card.

00:22:07.820 --> 00:22:12.480 align:middle line:84%
But I was 138 pounds when
my mother was diagnosed

00:22:12.480 --> 00:22:14.760 align:middle line:90%
with cancer November the 10th.

00:22:14.760 --> 00:22:17.672 align:middle line:84%
And she died February
17, and I was 219 pounds.

00:22:17.672 --> 00:22:18.630 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh my goodness.

00:22:18.630 --> 00:22:18.880 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: That's like--

00:22:18.880 --> 00:22:20.350 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: A very short
amount of time.

00:22:20.350 --> 00:22:20.560 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Yeah.

00:22:20.560 --> 00:22:21.976 align:middle line:84%
And I always say,
I would have had

00:22:21.976 --> 00:22:25.940 align:middle line:84%
to be mainlining entire
cakes in the closet.

00:22:25.940 --> 00:22:28.000 align:middle line:90%
But I wasn't.

00:22:28.000 --> 00:22:33.530 align:middle line:84%
And I know that the amount of
grief showed up in my body.

00:22:33.530 --> 00:22:38.050 align:middle line:84%
So I, like anyone else, went
on bazillions of diets, right?

00:22:38.050 --> 00:22:39.340 align:middle line:90%
You know, I'm going to diet.

00:22:39.340 --> 00:22:40.280 align:middle line:90%
And nothing worked.

00:22:40.280 --> 00:22:42.610 align:middle line:84%
I gained weight every
time I went on a diet.

00:22:42.610 --> 00:22:45.000 align:middle line:84%
So I finally-- it was
an interesting thing.

00:22:45.000 --> 00:22:48.970 align:middle line:84%
So that was when I dropped all
the weight was when I stopped

00:22:48.970 --> 00:22:51.740 align:middle line:84%
dieting and I decided
to love myself

00:22:51.740 --> 00:22:53.050 align:middle line:90%
instead of hating myself.

00:22:53.050 --> 00:22:55.872 align:middle line:84%
Because there was the
constant barrage of my own

00:22:55.872 --> 00:22:57.455 align:middle line:84%
mind even though I
was clean and sober

00:22:57.455 --> 00:22:59.199 align:middle line:90%
and my life was a miracle.

00:22:59.199 --> 00:23:01.240 align:middle line:84%
There was still this real
sense of low self-worth

00:23:01.240 --> 00:23:03.740 align:middle line:84%
because of my weight and
because of the pressure

00:23:03.740 --> 00:23:05.001 align:middle line:90%
to look a certain way, right?

00:23:05.001 --> 00:23:05.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:23:05.500 --> 00:23:07.940 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: Plus I was trying
to pursue a business where

00:23:07.940 --> 00:23:12.369 align:middle line:84%
it was just not going to
happen when I was, like, giant.

00:23:12.369 --> 00:23:13.660 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: In front of the camera?

00:23:13.660 --> 00:23:15.576 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: In front
of-- not any-- come on.

00:23:15.576 --> 00:23:16.577 align:middle line:90%
It was like, 219 pounds.

00:23:16.577 --> 00:23:18.784 align:middle line:84%
You're not going to go out
and be a rock star, right?

00:23:18.784 --> 00:23:19.610 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:23:19.610 --> 00:23:20.840 align:middle line:84%
Not unless you were
one first and then

00:23:20.840 --> 00:23:21.840 align:middle line:90%
you got to be one later.

00:23:21.840 --> 00:23:23.460 align:middle line:90%
I mean, that does not happen.

00:23:23.460 --> 00:23:25.860 align:middle line:84%
But it was this sense of
needing to protect myself,

00:23:25.860 --> 00:23:28.440 align:middle line:84%
and the body did exactly
what it was told.

00:23:28.440 --> 00:23:31.450 align:middle line:84%
I was unsafe from
my own thoughts.

00:23:31.450 --> 00:23:36.040 align:middle line:84%
So I went on this fascinating
year of self love.

00:23:36.040 --> 00:23:38.270 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, I'm not going
to hate myself anymore.

00:23:38.270 --> 00:23:39.350 align:middle line:90%
I went to Overeaters Anonymous.

00:23:39.350 --> 00:23:40.183 align:middle line:90%
That didn't help me.

00:23:40.183 --> 00:23:41.100 align:middle line:90%
I was just like, ugh.

00:23:41.100 --> 00:23:42.130 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You tried
diets, everything.

00:23:42.130 --> 00:23:43.130 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Oh my god.

00:23:43.130 --> 00:23:44.480 align:middle line:90%
You name every diet on the sun.

00:23:44.480 --> 00:23:46.977 align:middle line:84%
The Atkins Diet, the
only vegetable diet.

00:23:46.977 --> 00:23:47.810 align:middle line:90%
The grapefruit diet.

00:23:47.810 --> 00:23:48.503 align:middle line:90%
The egg diet.

00:23:48.503 --> 00:23:49.002 align:middle line:90%
I mean--

00:23:49.002 --> 00:23:50.360 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:23:50.360 --> 00:23:50.867 align:middle line:90%
The pills.

00:23:50.867 --> 00:23:53.200 align:middle line:84%
But I couldn't take pills
because I was clean and sober.

00:23:53.200 --> 00:23:54.560 align:middle line:90%
So that was before.

00:23:54.560 --> 00:23:56.027 align:middle line:84%
So now it's like,
what can I take

00:23:56.027 --> 00:23:57.860 align:middle line:84%
that was over the counter
that wasn't drugs?

00:23:57.860 --> 00:23:58.430 align:middle line:90%
So it was crazy.

00:23:58.430 --> 00:23:59.400 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you've been
through all of this

00:23:59.400 --> 00:24:01.360 align:middle line:84%
just to come to realize
that the self love

00:24:01.360 --> 00:24:02.620 align:middle line:90%
diet was the one that worked.

00:24:02.620 --> 00:24:02.810 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Oh, yeah.

00:24:02.810 --> 00:24:04.867 align:middle line:84%
Three meals, two
snacks, self love.

00:24:04.867 --> 00:24:05.950 align:middle line:90%
And I lost all the weight.

00:24:05.950 --> 00:24:08.940 align:middle line:84%
And stayed very slim
for a long time.

00:24:08.940 --> 00:24:09.780 align:middle line:90%
Like, you know.

00:24:09.780 --> 00:24:12.210 align:middle line:90%
So then, here's what's crazy.

00:24:12.210 --> 00:24:12.710 align:middle line:90%
So I--

00:24:12.710 --> 00:24:14.330 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We're going to get
back to that in just a second.

00:24:14.330 --> 00:24:15.820 align:middle line:90%
The three meals, the self love.

00:24:15.820 --> 00:24:17.570 align:middle line:84%
Because that's the
main point of the book.

00:24:17.570 --> 00:24:18.710 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: That's the
main point of the book.

00:24:18.710 --> 00:24:19.220 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: But then--

00:24:19.220 --> 00:24:20.470 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: But then-- wait.

00:24:20.470 --> 00:24:21.710 align:middle line:90%
This is the best part.

00:24:21.710 --> 00:24:22.710 align:middle line:90%
So I didn't even notice.

00:24:22.710 --> 00:24:24.890 align:middle line:84%
I just figured-- I
didn't even notice

00:24:24.890 --> 00:24:26.610 align:middle line:84%
I was doing that,
which was crazy.

00:24:26.610 --> 00:24:30.090 align:middle line:84%
I knew that that was-- all I
could do was just not diet,

00:24:30.090 --> 00:24:33.930 align:middle line:84%
love myself, stay sober,
and just surrender

00:24:33.930 --> 00:24:36.640 align:middle line:84%
to what God had put in front
of me, which was my readings.

00:24:36.640 --> 00:24:39.150 align:middle line:84%
And of course, I studied Jungian
psychology at that point.

00:24:39.150 --> 00:24:43.720 align:middle line:84%
I was voraciously snorting every
spiritual book I could get to.

00:24:43.720 --> 00:24:46.110 align:middle line:84%
I took meditation, I
went to the Tibetans,

00:24:46.110 --> 00:24:48.212 align:middle line:84%
I went to the Zens who
hit me with a stick,

00:24:48.212 --> 00:24:49.170 align:middle line:90%
and I didn't like them.

00:24:49.170 --> 00:24:51.086 align:middle line:84%
So I went back to the
Tibetans who were nicer.

00:24:51.086 --> 00:24:52.021 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:24:52.021 --> 00:24:52.520 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:24:52.520 --> 00:24:53.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Those were some Zens.

00:24:53.820 --> 00:24:53.990 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:24:53.990 --> 00:24:54.820 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: You know
what I'm saying, right?

00:24:54.820 --> 00:24:55.320 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:24:55.320 --> 00:24:57.220 align:middle line:84%
I was like, I don't
know about this, people.

00:24:57.220 --> 00:25:00.110 align:middle line:84%
So I just completely
immersed myself

00:25:00.110 --> 00:25:02.895 align:middle line:84%
in Louise Hay,
Marianne Williamson,

00:25:02.895 --> 00:25:04.590 align:middle line:84%
who are now all
my contemporaries.

00:25:04.590 --> 00:25:05.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Amazing.

00:25:05.380 --> 00:25:06.551 align:middle line:90%
Amazing, yes.

00:25:06.551 --> 00:25:07.050 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:25:07.050 --> 00:25:08.580 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: And then
wanted to understand

00:25:08.580 --> 00:25:10.705 align:middle line:84%
what was happening to me
when I was doing readings,

00:25:10.705 --> 00:25:12.870 align:middle line:84%
because I was so clearly
seeing these things.

00:25:12.870 --> 00:25:15.080 align:middle line:84%
And I was fascinated,
not with the information,

00:25:15.080 --> 00:25:17.140 align:middle line:84%
but what the people were
doing with their lives,

00:25:17.140 --> 00:25:19.672 align:middle line:84%
and why I saw certain
patterns, and what could I do,

00:25:19.672 --> 00:25:21.380 align:middle line:84%
and how could I
understand the symbolism,

00:25:21.380 --> 00:25:25.490 align:middle line:84%
and what does synchronicity
mean, and blah, blah, blah.

00:25:25.490 --> 00:25:29.652 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, I'm sure when
you're able to see intuitively

00:25:29.652 --> 00:25:31.860 align:middle line:84%
the pictures and how they
all line up, then of course

00:25:31.860 --> 00:25:33.740 align:middle line:84%
you're going to be
curious as to why.

00:25:33.740 --> 00:25:36.485 align:middle line:84%
And then people would want
help after that, right?

00:25:36.485 --> 00:25:38.110 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: I drove
my parents crazy.

00:25:38.110 --> 00:25:39.266 align:middle line:90%
My question was always why?

00:25:39.266 --> 00:25:39.766 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:25:39.766 --> 00:25:40.405 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:25:40.405 --> 00:25:41.005 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Why?

00:25:41.005 --> 00:25:41.505 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:25:41.505 --> 00:25:42.120 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Why, why, why?

00:25:42.120 --> 00:25:42.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:25:42.400 --> 00:25:42.899 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:25:42.899 --> 00:25:44.275 align:middle line:84%
Why people do the
things they do.

00:25:44.275 --> 00:25:45.024 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Why?

00:25:45.024 --> 00:25:46.070 align:middle line:90%
Why do I have to do that.

00:25:46.070 --> 00:25:46.986 align:middle line:90%
Why is this happening?

00:25:46.986 --> 00:25:47.980 align:middle line:90%
Why, why, why?

00:25:47.980 --> 00:25:48.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Exactly.

00:25:48.690 --> 00:25:50.330 align:middle line:84%
I'm right there
with you, sister.

00:25:50.330 --> 00:25:51.164 align:middle line:90%
Endless fascination.

00:25:51.164 --> 00:25:51.955 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Yeah.

00:25:51.955 --> 00:25:52.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:25:52.730 --> 00:25:55.290 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: So then what
happens is, OK, at that point

00:25:55.290 --> 00:25:56.800 align:middle line:84%
I'd given up
completely the music.

00:25:56.800 --> 00:25:57.370 align:middle line:90%
Forget that.

00:25:57.370 --> 00:25:58.670 align:middle line:90%
I was like, so not about that.

00:25:58.670 --> 00:26:00.950 align:middle line:84%
So I was fascinated
with the chakras.

00:26:00.950 --> 00:26:04.400 align:middle line:84%
So I'd started studying Anodea
Judith's work and Caroline

00:26:04.400 --> 00:26:05.980 align:middle line:90%
Myss.

00:26:05.980 --> 00:26:09.980 align:middle line:84%
Anodea Judith wrote "Western
Body, Eastern Mind,"

00:26:09.980 --> 00:26:11.930 align:middle line:84%
and "The Anatomy of the
Spirit" was Caroline.

00:26:11.930 --> 00:26:13.980 align:middle line:84%
So I completely
when chakra crazy.

00:26:13.980 --> 00:26:16.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, two very good
people though to study,

00:26:16.170 --> 00:26:18.480 align:middle line:84%
because they're
both very authentic.

00:26:18.480 --> 00:26:19.970 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Absolutely.

00:26:19.970 --> 00:26:22.130 align:middle line:84%
I created "Journey Through
the Chakras," which

00:26:22.130 --> 00:26:26.520 align:middle line:84%
was the first time anybody
had recorded multi track

00:26:26.520 --> 00:26:30.720 align:middle line:84%
spiritual CD, you know, like
you would a regular rock album.

00:26:30.720 --> 00:26:33.930 align:middle line:84%
And it went to number one in
Canada because I'm Canadian.

00:26:33.930 --> 00:26:38.680 align:middle line:84%
And EMI Music picked it
up in these very strange

00:26:38.680 --> 00:26:40.420 align:middle line:90%
sychronistic series.

00:26:40.420 --> 00:26:45.950 align:middle line:84%
I had met Eric Ross, who worked
with Tori Amos on her big break

00:26:45.950 --> 00:26:46.927 align:middle line:90%
out album.

00:26:46.927 --> 00:26:48.760 align:middle line:84%
"Little Earthquakes,"
I think it was called.

00:26:48.760 --> 00:26:51.960 align:middle line:84%
And he really developed
her sound, et cetera.

00:26:51.960 --> 00:26:55.570 align:middle line:84%
He did the soundtrack for
this documentary I was in.

00:26:55.570 --> 00:26:56.800 align:middle line:90%
So I approached him.

00:26:56.800 --> 00:26:58.500 align:middle line:84%
EMI picked me up
and said, you know,

00:26:58.500 --> 00:27:01.622 align:middle line:84%
we want you to do another
spiritual kind of chanting CD,

00:27:01.622 --> 00:27:03.080 align:middle line:84%
which was what they
were expecting.

00:27:03.080 --> 00:27:04.730 align:middle line:90%
I went to Eric.

00:27:04.730 --> 00:27:06.640 align:middle line:90%
And he knew I could sing.

00:27:06.640 --> 00:27:08.080 align:middle line:90%
He goes, we're not doing that.

00:27:08.080 --> 00:27:09.260 align:middle line:90%
We're going to write music.

00:27:09.260 --> 00:27:10.240 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, we are?

00:27:10.240 --> 00:27:11.530 align:middle line:90%
So we recorded these songs.

00:27:11.530 --> 00:27:13.690 align:middle line:90%
I went back to Canada sweating.

00:27:13.690 --> 00:27:16.930 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, I'm really
sorry I recorded these songs.

00:27:16.930 --> 00:27:17.710 align:middle line:90%
I'm so sorry.

00:27:17.710 --> 00:27:19.170 align:middle line:84%
I have to give you
your money back.

00:27:19.170 --> 00:27:21.030 align:middle line:84%
And I know you wanted me to do
this, like, new age-y thing.

00:27:21.030 --> 00:27:23.400 align:middle line:84%
And the president of EMI
Music said, oh my god.

00:27:23.400 --> 00:27:24.200 align:middle line:90%
This is so good.

00:27:24.200 --> 00:27:25.800 align:middle line:84%
But we're not going to
tell anybody who you are.

00:27:25.800 --> 00:27:28.070 align:middle line:84%
We're going to send it
around to the A&R department,

00:27:28.070 --> 00:27:28.710 align:middle line:90%
see what they think.

00:27:28.710 --> 00:27:31.043 align:middle line:84%
And if everybody likes it,
we're putting you on a plane.

00:27:31.043 --> 00:27:34.270 align:middle line:84%
And if they don't, we want
to go back to do what we did.

00:27:34.270 --> 00:27:35.700 align:middle line:90%
So I was like, OK.

00:27:35.700 --> 00:27:38.030 align:middle line:84%
They came back and said,
we're getting you on a plane.

00:27:38.030 --> 00:27:39.170 align:middle line:90%
Go back to Los Angeles.

00:27:39.170 --> 00:27:41.950 align:middle line:84%
So I recorded, in seven
weeks, I wrote and recorded

00:27:41.950 --> 00:27:46.740 align:middle line:84%
a whole album with EMI
called "Magdalene's Garden."

00:27:46.740 --> 00:27:47.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Whoa.

00:27:47.870 --> 00:27:48.661 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Yeah.

00:27:48.661 --> 00:27:50.960 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And this was infusing
the chakras into music?

00:27:50.960 --> 00:27:53.200 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: No, that was the
first album that got me there.

00:27:53.200 --> 00:27:54.700 align:middle line:84%
No, this was just
singer songwriter.

00:27:54.700 --> 00:27:58.040 align:middle line:84%
It was music that was all
about, interestingly enough,

00:27:58.040 --> 00:28:00.040 align:middle line:84%
it was all about
relationships, but relationship

00:28:00.040 --> 00:28:00.750 align:middle line:90%
to your spirit.

00:28:00.750 --> 00:28:02.475 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Did that other
one ever get produced?

00:28:02.475 --> 00:28:03.240 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Oh, yeah.

00:28:03.240 --> 00:28:03.450 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:28:03.450 --> 00:28:05.330 align:middle line:84%
It was number one. "Journey
Through the Chakras."

00:28:05.330 --> 00:28:05.870 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh, that was "Journey
Through the Chakras."

00:28:05.870 --> 00:28:07.911 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: Yeah, it
was the number one seller.

00:28:07.911 --> 00:28:09.820 align:middle line:84%
It still is a
classic seller now.

00:28:09.820 --> 00:28:10.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Great.

00:28:10.560 --> 00:28:12.185 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: That
was a meditation CD,

00:28:12.185 --> 00:28:13.090 align:middle line:90%
so that still sells.

00:28:13.090 --> 00:28:17.320 align:middle line:84%
But the interesting thing was,
I tried to quit doing readings,

00:28:17.320 --> 00:28:19.540 align:middle line:84%
but the music business
wasn't for me.

00:28:19.540 --> 00:28:22.150 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Why?

00:28:22.150 --> 00:28:24.620 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: Because
I got what I wanted,

00:28:24.620 --> 00:28:26.080 align:middle line:90%
which was not through that.

00:28:26.080 --> 00:28:28.780 align:middle line:84%
I proved to myself
that I could sing.

00:28:28.780 --> 00:28:31.930 align:middle line:84%
The business was going
to eat me alive in order

00:28:31.930 --> 00:28:33.750 align:middle line:90%
for me to stay clean and sober.

00:28:33.750 --> 00:28:37.050 align:middle line:84%
And plus, I was already doing
so well as an intuitive.

00:28:37.050 --> 00:28:39.750 align:middle line:84%
And I wasn't about to go
sit in a van with a band

00:28:39.750 --> 00:28:42.820 align:middle line:90%
and go to bar to bar to sing.

00:28:42.820 --> 00:28:46.140 align:middle line:90%
It just wasn't me.

00:28:46.140 --> 00:28:49.590 align:middle line:84%
And the CD was up against
Britney Spears and Christina

00:28:49.590 --> 00:28:51.820 align:middle line:84%
Aguilera, and I
sound like Kate Bush.

00:28:51.820 --> 00:28:55.150 align:middle line:84%
So it didn't do well
anyway, which is fine.

00:28:55.150 --> 00:28:56.540 align:middle line:90%
But I'm very proud of it.

00:28:56.540 --> 00:28:57.630 align:middle line:90%
People love it today.

00:28:57.630 --> 00:28:59.250 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But you said you got
what you wanted out of it.

00:28:59.250 --> 00:28:59.990 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: I
got what I wanted,

00:28:59.990 --> 00:29:02.360 align:middle line:84%
which is to prove to
me that I was talented.

00:29:02.360 --> 00:29:05.710 align:middle line:84%
But also, I was chasing
something for those years

00:29:05.710 --> 00:29:08.510 align:middle line:84%
that I got out of my
recovery and I got out

00:29:08.510 --> 00:29:10.670 align:middle line:84%
of-- I wanted to feel
good about myself.

00:29:10.670 --> 00:29:12.440 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to feel like I counted.

00:29:12.440 --> 00:29:14.430 align:middle line:84%
And I thought music,
because of course it

00:29:14.430 --> 00:29:16.690 align:middle line:84%
was quite narcissistic
in the early years.

00:29:16.690 --> 00:29:20.923 align:middle line:84%
I just wanted to sing
about my life and my pain.

00:29:20.923 --> 00:29:21.422 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:29:21.422 --> 00:29:21.921 align:middle line:90%
Ah--

00:29:21.921 --> 00:29:22.850 align:middle line:90%
[GUITAR SOUND]

00:29:22.850 --> 00:29:25.220 align:middle line:84%
And then in the end, I
didn't need to do that.

00:29:25.220 --> 00:29:27.030 align:middle line:90%
I wrote some awesome music.

00:29:27.030 --> 00:29:31.040 align:middle line:84%
But I was getting the value
for my life out of my readings.

00:29:31.040 --> 00:29:32.950 align:middle line:90%
I loved doing it.

00:29:32.950 --> 00:29:34.650 align:middle line:84%
And yet, I still kind
of tried to quit.

00:29:34.650 --> 00:29:38.210 align:middle line:84%
Then W Magazine wrote a whole
full page article about me.

00:29:38.210 --> 00:29:42.860 align:middle line:84%
And then I got to Hay House
and basically, Reid Tracy,

00:29:42.860 --> 00:29:46.074 align:middle line:84%
who completely changed my life
in one minute, who I love,

00:29:46.074 --> 00:29:47.740 align:middle line:84%
said to me, you can't
serve two masters.

00:29:47.740 --> 00:29:49.290 align:middle line:84%
They're going to think
you're a singing psychic.

00:29:49.290 --> 00:29:50.600 align:middle line:90%
You know what I'm saying?

00:29:50.600 --> 00:29:51.501 align:middle line:90%
I was like, oh.

00:29:51.501 --> 00:29:52.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: He is brilliant.

00:29:52.500 --> 00:29:52.740 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:29:52.740 --> 00:29:53.531 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Yeah.

00:29:53.531 --> 00:29:55.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:29:55.770 --> 00:29:58.000 align:middle line:84%
You obviously don't
have a problem talking,

00:29:58.000 --> 00:29:58.720 align:middle line:90%
which is great.

00:29:58.720 --> 00:29:59.090 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: No.

00:29:59.090 --> 00:29:59.790 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you were
worried that you

00:29:59.790 --> 00:30:00.710 align:middle line:84%
were going to have
to fill in, right?

00:30:00.710 --> 00:30:01.585 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No, I wasn't.

00:30:01.585 --> 00:30:03.000 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:30:03.000 --> 00:30:06.840 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you really have many,
many different gifts in a way.

00:30:06.840 --> 00:30:08.235 align:middle line:90%
And you called them attributes?

00:30:08.235 --> 00:30:09.670 align:middle line:90%
What did you call them?

00:30:09.670 --> 00:30:10.670 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Aptitudes.

00:30:10.670 --> 00:30:11.070 align:middle line:90%
Or attributes.

00:30:11.070 --> 00:30:11.570 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:30:11.570 --> 00:30:12.820 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, aptitudes.

00:30:12.820 --> 00:30:14.310 align:middle line:90%
I've got the gift of gab.

00:30:14.310 --> 00:30:16.040 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You can
talk, you can sing,

00:30:16.040 --> 00:30:18.060 align:middle line:90%
you can read people's lives.

00:30:18.060 --> 00:30:21.886 align:middle line:84%
And this is how you come
across, as completely authentic.

00:30:21.886 --> 00:30:23.636 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: I don't
know how else to be.

00:30:23.636 --> 00:30:24.311 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:30:24.311 --> 00:30:25.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I was going
to ask you that.

00:30:25.810 --> 00:30:27.850 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: I'm the
same onstage, offstage,

00:30:27.850 --> 00:30:29.020 align:middle line:90%
on the radio, off the radio.

00:30:29.020 --> 00:30:29.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right here.

00:30:29.580 --> 00:30:30.621 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Right here.

00:30:30.621 --> 00:30:32.240 align:middle line:10%
I mean, you know what I do?

00:30:32.240 --> 00:30:33.520 align:middle line:10%
I love people.

00:30:33.520 --> 00:30:34.760 align:middle line:10%
I've got to say this, OK?

00:30:34.760 --> 00:30:36.432 align:middle line:10%
I came from a lot of pain.

00:30:36.432 --> 00:30:37.640 align:middle line:10%
I don't want to live in pain.

00:30:37.640 --> 00:30:38.570 align:middle line:10%
I'm not a victim.

00:30:38.570 --> 00:30:41.260 align:middle line:10%
I completely see
what happened to me,

00:30:41.260 --> 00:30:43.370 align:middle line:10%
how my addictions
worked into that.

00:30:43.370 --> 00:30:46.060 align:middle line:84%
And I know today that I was
given a second chance at life,

00:30:46.060 --> 00:30:47.470 align:middle line:84%
and I am not going
to walk around

00:30:47.470 --> 00:30:49.124 align:middle line:84%
with a great big
rock on my shoulder

00:30:49.124 --> 00:30:50.540 align:middle line:84%
because some stuff
happened to me.

00:30:50.540 --> 00:30:51.820 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't have
kids because of it.

00:30:51.820 --> 00:30:53.278 align:middle line:84%
I got a serious
illness afterwards.

00:30:53.278 --> 00:30:53.990 align:middle line:90%
Blah, blah, blah.

00:30:53.990 --> 00:30:54.770 align:middle line:90%
But you know what?

00:30:54.770 --> 00:30:59.894 align:middle line:84%
I get today that life-- you can
make lemonade out of lemons.

00:30:59.894 --> 00:31:00.810 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You sure have.

00:31:00.810 --> 00:31:05.980 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: You can, and
I'm not driven by my stories.

00:31:05.980 --> 00:31:08.770 align:middle line:84%
You know, that's a story,
but it doesn't define me.

00:31:08.770 --> 00:31:11.520 align:middle line:84%
