00:39:02.890 --> 00:39:06.170 align:middle line:84%
We get something called
visceral fat around our middle.

00:39:06.170 --> 00:39:08.071 align:middle line:84%
And because we have
to eat something--

00:39:08.071 --> 00:39:09.570 align:middle line:84%
and that's the way
to keep us alive.

00:39:09.570 --> 00:39:13.255 align:middle line:84%
That's how ancient humans
didn't-- you know what I mean?

00:39:13.255 --> 00:39:15.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Freeze in the winter.

00:39:15.080 --> 00:39:15.580 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:39:15.580 --> 00:39:18.419 align:middle line:84%
>>BARON-REID: So for some
of us, for some of us

00:39:18.419 --> 00:39:19.960 align:middle line:84%
who are under that
constant low grade

00:39:19.960 --> 00:39:23.470 align:middle line:84%
stress, when you're
going to gain weight.

00:39:23.470 --> 00:39:24.839 align:middle line:90%
Not everybody.

00:39:24.839 --> 00:39:26.630 align:middle line:84%
There's a lucky part
of the population that

00:39:26.630 --> 00:39:28.200 align:middle line:84%
goes the opposite
extreme, right?

00:39:28.200 --> 00:39:29.050 align:middle line:90%
So they won't.

00:39:29.050 --> 00:39:30.150 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:39:30.150 --> 00:39:33.105 align:middle line:84%
And we'll typically use food to
ground ourselves after 4:00 PM.

00:39:33.105 --> 00:39:34.230 align:middle line:90%
So people who are empathic.

00:39:34.230 --> 00:39:35.470 align:middle line:90%
4 o'clock, the bell rings.

00:39:35.470 --> 00:39:36.610 align:middle line:90%
I can't take this anymore.

00:39:36.610 --> 00:39:37.280 align:middle line:90%
Give me some food.

00:39:37.280 --> 00:39:37.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:39:37.870 --> 00:39:38.170 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:39:38.170 --> 00:39:39.500 align:middle line:84%
Because you can hold
off for that long.

00:39:39.500 --> 00:39:41.250 align:middle line:84%
But also that fat
stores around the middle

00:39:41.250 --> 00:39:42.610 align:middle line:90%
because it protects the organs.

00:39:42.610 --> 00:39:43.610 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Correct.

00:39:43.610 --> 00:39:44.300 align:middle line:90%
Correct.

00:39:44.300 --> 00:39:46.090 align:middle line:84%
And visceral fat makes
more visceral fat,

00:39:46.090 --> 00:39:47.410 align:middle line:84%
so that's why it's
harder to lose weight.

00:39:47.410 --> 00:39:49.410 align:middle line:84%
So when you're telling your
body when you're on a diet--

00:39:49.410 --> 00:39:51.784 align:middle line:84%
and this is for anybody that's
gained weight when they've

00:39:51.784 --> 00:39:54.250 align:middle line:84%
dieted and not just
empathic people-- you're

00:39:54.250 --> 00:39:55.590 align:middle line:90%
telling your body you hate it.

00:39:55.590 --> 00:39:57.381 align:middle line:84%
The body's going to
go, we need protection.

00:39:57.381 --> 00:39:59.330 align:middle line:84%
We need to protect
her from her thoughts.

00:39:59.330 --> 00:40:01.530 align:middle line:84%
So you constantly give
yourself more stress.

00:40:01.530 --> 00:40:02.780 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: We're going to starve.

00:40:02.780 --> 00:40:04.392 align:middle line:90%
Hold on to what we have.

00:40:04.392 --> 00:40:05.350 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: God, yes.

00:40:05.350 --> 00:40:05.800 align:middle line:90%
Hello.

00:40:05.800 --> 00:40:06.850 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: She's not
going to feed us again.

00:40:06.850 --> 00:40:07.434 align:middle line:90%
Let's hold on.

00:40:07.434 --> 00:40:08.225 align:middle line:90%
>>BARON-REID: Yeah.

00:40:08.225 --> 00:40:08.970 align:middle line:90%
And then, oh boy.

00:40:08.970 --> 00:40:09.640 align:middle line:90%
She's going to feed us now.

00:40:09.640 --> 00:40:10.970 align:middle line:90%
We'd better hold on that, too.

00:40:10.970 --> 00:40:12.490 align:middle line:90%
But not just that.

00:40:12.490 --> 00:40:16.170 align:middle line:84%
When you're trying to starve,
and you're hating your body,

00:40:16.170 --> 00:40:17.990 align:middle line:84%
you notice these
very stick thin women

00:40:17.990 --> 00:40:19.910 align:middle line:84%
with these bloated
bellies, right?

00:40:19.910 --> 00:40:21.140 align:middle line:90%
And you can see that too.

00:40:21.140 --> 00:40:22.580 align:middle line:90%
So it's just fascinating.

00:40:22.580 --> 00:40:25.100 align:middle line:84%
And I did all the
studies because it

00:40:25.100 --> 00:40:26.940 align:middle line:90%
was a departure from my work.

00:40:26.940 --> 00:40:28.950 align:middle line:84%
My work was very
psychological and it

00:40:28.950 --> 00:40:30.860 align:middle line:84%
was about omens and
signs and symbolism

00:40:30.860 --> 00:40:32.580 align:middle line:90%
